Nigerian dancer Love Divine has died of electrocution on Wednesday. The dancer popularly known as Kodak was reportedly in the home of music video director, Clarence Peters when she was electrocuted while charging her phone. Sources said Kodak was working on a production when the incident occurred. She had taken a break to plug her phone downstairs when she got electrocuted and was rushed to hospital where she was pronounced dead. Also, a man identified as Olaniyi Banjoko, 56, was on Wednesday evening electrocuted while doing laundry at Ikorodu, Lagos. It was gathered that the deceased was electrocuted by a protection rod of a shop in front of their residence. Police spokesman Bala Elkana said the case was reported by a relative of the deceased.